Ridgeway College in Louis Trichardt once again celebrates outstanding performance by their matric class of 2021 in their National Senior Certificate (NSC) examinations written with the International Examinations Board. The college’s top achiever was Dede Bessong, who achieved seven distinctions - for accounting, Afrikaans First Additional Langue (FAL), English Home Langue (HL), life orientation, life sciences, mathematics, and physical sciences. Tendani Sinyosi and Tinashe Kujinga each received six distinctions. Tendani achieved distinctions in accounting, Afrikaans (FAL), life orientation, life sciences, mathematics and physical sciences. Tinashe achieved his distinctions in accounting, English (HL), geography, life orientation, mathematics and physical sciences. Nyikwana Baloyi achieved five distinctions in accounting, Afrikaans (FAL), life orientation, life sciences and mathematics, while Nsovo Marivate, Risuna Shivambi, and Bella Ntini each achieved four distinctions. In addition, Ridgeway College had three candidates placed in the Top 1% of candidates nationally. They are Tendani Sinyosi (advanced programme mathematics/AP maths and physical sciences), Dede Bessong (English Home Language) and Mashudu Tshibudzi (Xitsonga First Additional Langue). “To these, and all pupils from the Class of 2021, Ridgeway College congratulates you on your achievements and we look forward to hearing of your continued success,” said the college. 